Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
1214 Military Rd Muckenburra (Gingin) off Wanneroo Rd, ticks all the boxes for a market garden. Approximately 90 km north of Perth and 30 minutes' drive from Wanneroo, it is an easy commute for staff and close to support services.

Comprising 81Ha* of flat (majority cleared) grey over yellow sand, it is an easy property to work up and has been previously used as a market garden.

The property comes with a 448,000kL* Ground Water License (superficial swan) with three phase power to the centre of the property.

This is a genuine sale, all offers to include GST.

The property is for sale by Offers To Purchase.

*approx.

Lot 104 Brand Highway & Lot 105 Whitfield Springs Road

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Lot 104 Brand Highway Beermullah and Lot 105 Whitfield Springs Road Beermullah, known as Whitfield Springs Farm is for sale by Offers to Purchase.

Whitfield Springs Farm, comprises two titles, Lot 104 comprising 112.40Ha* and Lot 105 comprising 315.50Ha*.

Whitfield Springs Farms has been used to propagate Paulownia and Sheoak trees.

Lot 104 has frontage to the Brand Highway with a 464,250kL ground water licence which permits the irrigation of up to 96.6hHa* of Paulownia trees. The improvements on Lot 104 comprise bores, pump shed and irrigation system.

Lot 105 is an undeveloped allotment adjoining Lot 104 and has no impact on the operation of the Paulownia plantation. Lot 5 is available for sale either individually or as a parcel with Lot 104.

LOCATION

Whitfield Springs Farm is located 130km* north of Perth in the Gingin shire. The township of Gingin is located approximately 25km* of the properties.

The Shire of Gingin covering an area of 3,325 square kilometres and has a population in excess of 4,500. Gingin is one of the fastest growing and developing rural shires in Western Australia, and has a strategic location to the immediate north of the City of Wanneroo.

PROPERTY SUMMARY

Whitfield Springs Farm is an approximate 427.90Ha*landholding comprising the following Certificates of Title:

- Volume 2719 Folio 680 known as Lot 104, 5731 Brand Highway Beermullah, WA (112.40Ha*)
- Volume 2719 Folio 681 known as Lot 105, Whitfield Springs Road, Beermullah, WA (315.50Ha*).

Lot 104 has a Paulownia plantation established on approximately 96.6Ha*.

Lot 105 is undeveloped with native vegetation covering 100% of the property.

Whitfield Springs Farm will appeal to the commercial operator wishing to take advantage of the irrigation infrastructure likely to suit olive, lucerne or market garden operators and the undeveloped lot 105 will appeal to the lifestyle market.

*approx.
